; Real-browser e2e for the site example — pure OCaml/Eio, no npm. Drives a headless
; Chrome over the DevTools Protocol (cdp.ml = a hand-written WebSocket+CDP client on
; Eio). NOT part of `dune test` (it needs a system Chrome); run via ./run.sh.
(executable
 (name e2e)
 (modules e2e cdp)
 (libraries eio eio_main eio.unix yojson base64)
 (flags (:standard -w +a-26-27-32-33-37-69-70)))
